<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n54106b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54106b">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54106b"> 106(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Safa Hill</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">On account of the insulting behaviour of their enemies the Moslems had, for some time past, given up praying in public; they used to meet secretly in the house of a convert named al-Arkam. This house, situated on the <mark>hills of Safa</mark>, away from the center of the town, came to be became known as the &ldquo;House of Islam.&rdquo; <small> Edith Holland, <a name="EHSM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EHSM"><cite title="source">The Story of Mohammed</cite></a> (1914) 54-55</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
